compounddef.innerclass: TfTypeFunctions< Ptr< T >, std::enable_if_t< std::is_base_of< TfWeakPtrFacadeBase, Ptr< T > >::value > >
TfTypeFunctions< Ptr< const T >, std::enable_if_t< std::is_base_of< TfWeakPtrFacadeBase, Ptr< const T > >::value > >

sect1.title: comparisons
sect1.para: These are provided both to avoid ambiguous overloads due to TfWeakPtrFacade::Derived comparisons with TfRefPtr and because implicitly converting a nullptr to a TfWeakPtrFacade-derived type can add an unknown amount of overhead.
